Lesson 

---------- [L1]

Video link: https://youtu.be/eTHDZWAJxPA
Audio link: https://rss.com/podcasts/footnerdprogram/560903/

Creators: Tom Williams, James Dooner

Framework:
- "play is the way" It's how we create sustainable movement patterns
- defining play
- Dr. Stuart Brown: Play is more than fun
- history of play
- play and building risk tolerance
- play is innate in mammals in order to teach skills of survival 
- returning to play

Resources: 
Book: Play by Dr. Stuart Brown
Book: Playing With Movement by Todd Hargrove
Book: Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience by Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi


Audio lesson notes:
- detailed notes and timestamps from the audio lesson


Experiments (nano to macro)
- write in your health log about your relationship to play
- for the next 10 days, create a movement play date by yourself or with others
- share your experience with other nerds in Slack or Nerd office hours
- if you haven't already, create a place in your movement practice to incorporate play 


